Re: AoW strat</span><hr size=1> Ardur is right. Practice on the Idol unslowed. He's similar to the Avatar but no flurries and has less HP. If you can kill the Idol unslowed fairly easily, you may have a good shot at the Avatar. If you kill the Idol slowed without practicing it, then expect the other guilds on your server to hate you for blowing the Avatar spawn for them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub117.ezboard.com/udummywummy01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dummywummy01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/30/02 7:41:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub117.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12055.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoW strat</span><hr size=1> Only other guild on my server is mostly full of jerkoffs, i have no problem with blowing AoW <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub117.ezboard.com/uislington.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Islington</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/30/02 8:02:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub117.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12055.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoW strat</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Only other guild on my server is mostly full of jerkoffs, i have no problem with blowing AoW <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  Fight it Unslowed anyway.  It gives you a chance to perfect your strat and technique and you can try over and over and over again until you have it right.  The Idol is a perfect Mob to practice on because the AOW is simply in an unreal Mob.  You can practice positioning and tactics as long as it takes and when you kill it easily, unslowed, you know you at least have the ability to kill AOW.<br><br>Slow the Idol?  You learn nothing and you get to wipe out to AOW without ever really testing yourself or learning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub117.ezboard.com/udeanob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deanob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/30/02 11:02:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub117.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12055.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> a tip</span><hr size=1> A little tip for you.  Although idol's DPS output is almost the same.  That flurry makes it much harder.  When you add the flurry to that kind of DPS.  It gives you spikes of damage.  In that case.. sometimes you can get very lucky and not get a double flurry after a full hitting quad (not including reposts) and sometimes your unlucky.  That will make or break keeping your MT alive.  (unless he has 8k hp)<br><br>The fight has to do with some luck for the new crowd.<br><br>Also, unless you got your CH rotations down.  Try looking up a tactic about duel CH rotations.  Might help you if you dont got any tanks 7.3k hp +.<br><br><a href="http://www.fiveassedmonkey.net">Grey Hawke</a><br>If you want to check out some tactics.  Dont think we have them posted yet but check the warriors site in a few days.  Might have 